getAgentId

java.util.UUID getAgentId()
Return the ID of this agent.

All agents have a unique ID that can be used to identify them. This ID is guaranteed to be unique across space and time. This means that if an agent of type A is created, deleted, then re-created with the same instance name it will get a new ID.

The ID can always be used to identify an agent. The combination of instance name and agent type are usually unique, but not guaranteed to be so.

Returns:
This agent's unique ID.

java.lang.String getAgentType()

Returns:
Which kind of agent this is

getInstanceName

java.lang.String getInstanceName()
Return the instance name of this agent.

The instance name of an agent is the user-provided name that is assigned when the agent is created. See AgentMetadataService2.getUnqualifiedInstanceName()

Returns:
The agent's instance name.

getLastKnownState

AgentLifecycleState getLastKnownState()
The last known state of the agent. This will return a cached state value if available. Note, that the agent may not actually be in this state. See getActualState() if you need to know the current state.

Returns:
the last known agent state value

getLocalAgentImpl

<LocalAgent extends Agent> LocalAgent getLocalAgentImpl(java.lang.Class<LocalAgent> agentClass)
                                           throws NotLocalAgentException
Provides access to the Agent implementation if the controlling agent and the remote agent are part of the same deployment and both are running on the local Agent Manager instance isAgentInstanceLocal(). The returned value will allow the caller to invoke any implemented methods available on the LocalAgent interface. This will allow fine grain control of the agent with respect to properties changes and other implementation specific activities

Type Parameters:
LocalAgent - Devkit Agent implementation of the agent to be controlled
Parameters:
agentClass - The known implementing class of the Agent instance active in the local Agent Manager instance
Returns:
A reference to the local Agent implementation instance
Throws:
NotLocalAgentException - If the Agent instance is not present on this Agent Manager instance

isAgentInstanceLocal

boolean isAgentInstanceLocal()
Check if this RemoteAgentProxy is representing an Agent on the local Agent Manager instance and is part part of the same deployed AgentPackage as the Agent instance that is invoking this Service.

Returns:
true if agent implementation can be controlled locally
